        "text": "for us from thence",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". From this it is apparent that the hitherto abundant flocks and herds of the patriarchal family had been greatly reduced by the long-continued and severe drought, thus requiring them to obtain food from Egypt, if either any portion of their flocks were to be saved, or themselves to escape starvation, as the patriarch explained to his sons. ",
        "children": []
